<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4643216>
    dc:description "Fig. 8. – A–C. Hooks of Apionsoma (Apionsoma) hespera (Chamberlin, 1920) comb. nov. A. From Oaxaca, Mexico. B–C. From Peru. – D–E. Hooks of Apionsoma misakianum (Ikeda, 1904). D. From Misaki, Japan. E. From Japan. B–C: from Amor (1975); D: from Ikeda (1904); E: from Cutler et al. (1984)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4643216/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4643218>
    dc:description "Fig. 9. Apionsoma (Apionsoma) hespera (Chamberlin, 1920) comb. nov. from the Southern Mexican Pacific. A. External morphology. B. Internal morphology. C. Caudal papillae. D. Caudal papillae, amplified view. E. Hooks. Abbreviations: DRM = dorsal retractor muscles; I = intestine; LM = longitudinal muscle; N = nephridium; VRM = ventral retractor muscles." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4643218/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

